Class StraightPipe

  • java.lang.Object
    • dangerzone.blocks.Block
      • blocks.Pipe
        • blocks.StraightPipe
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PusherStraightPipe

    public class StraightPipe
extends Pipe
    Straight pipes are one of three basic kinds of pipes, which supply blocks and items to powered devices they are attached to. Like other pipes, straight pipes are placed with their output end facing up. They are solid, and cannot be broken without a pickaxe. Straight pipes draw items from the face that is opposite of their output face.
    Author:
    eaglgenes101
